Happy birthday Superman. I often wonder what life would be like if you were still here. I also question why you??? Since you left, your oldest daughter @tiaresade is very responsible, hard working, stable, and takes care of all of us. Your youngest daughter @__ajeeeeee is engaged, has 4 boys, and she is the perfect mom, her life revolves around them. And guess what they all look like you 😊. Your baby boy Jeremiah is turning 8 next month and your mini me Ja’meer is 12 and they both act so much like you. My mom is doing good, she hasn’t been sick in a while, and she misses you and talks about you alot. But don’t worry I got her! 😉 As for me, I became “BriElle Lesley”. I’m still doing music! Since you left, I’ve dropped an album and a bunch of music and music videos. I’ve traveled done many interviews and performed in a lot of beautiful places. I still haven’t made it yet but I’ve come a long way… and still going. My daughters, Peyton 11, and Peysley 10, are growing so fast and are almost taller than me. Idk if they remember you forreal but they know who you are, I tell them stories about how over protective you were with them and how they were your first grand babies and you kept them with you more than anybody. I really wish you were here to help me raise them tho. You were the perfect dad, and I just wish they could’ve had a piece of that. I still think of you EVERYTIME something goes wrong. Like “Man if my daddy was here…” but it only makes things worse. I started cooking publicly. People would ask me where did I learn to cook and I’d tell them how you had me in the kitchen at 7 years old. I’m a lot like you daddy, you gave me all the best parts of you. Your voice, your skills, your personality, your ambition, your ability to just make stuff happen and Im a great mom! I’m so grateful for you, I had the best childhood and the best memories because of you and my mom. Y’all were the perfect pair for me. I am who I am because I had amazing parents, and even tho our time together was cut short, im full of gratitude because I had the best daddy in the world! I love you so much! I miss you everyday, and until we meet again, watch over us! 😉🤞🏽❤️‍🩹 👑

Transparent post:
I just want to take this time to Thank GOD in front of everybody…. As some of you may already know I made a big move last week. I left my hometown Detroit and moved to Atlanta. I’ve been saying I was going to do this for over 7 years now, and each time I would say I had to get myself together first or I’d end up talking myself out of it before even actually thinking it all the way through. I love my city Detroit, it is all I know, but I was too comfortable there and I saw no growth for me, I feel like Detroit has given me all that it could and I’m forever grateful for that. Moving to Atlanta was random. I didn’t prepare, I didn’t talk about it, I just woke up one day last month, telling myself it’s time to go, idk what came over me and made me actually take action this time but I couldn’t think about doing anything else. I didn’t tell anybody until I signed my new lease and then I sent out invitations to a farewell gathering at my house. I gave nobody a warning or even told anyone my plans I just got up and did it because I was already scared and I needed the little bit of courage I had to last me long enough to get through it. In my family I’ve always been the “Golden Child” even as an adult my family has always been very supportive and there. So I couldn’t reveal my plans until I actually had no other choice but to go. I didn’t want to risk anybody talking me out of my focus. Now I’m here, and I don’t regret one bit of it. I miss my friends, and family, but other than that, I’m just so grateful. My house, my kids school, the entire environment is everything and more than I imagined it be. I came here with no plan lol (how irresponsible is that 🤭) but I’m here off pure faith. GOD got me and he shows me everyday that I’m here, cause everything has gone so smoothly. It’s like I was suppose to been here. Procrastination and fear is what kept me in the box for so long. Now I’m free, and I ready for whateva! I’m so thankful!  My advice to my follower. Trust GOD, no matter how bad it can be, just know that he won’t let it. All my life people has taken care of me, I left that in Detroit. THIS ONE IS ON ME and Imma make it count! Blessings 😘

Transparency post:
Since my move, the devil has been busy… trying to put me back into a place of depression, discourage me, fill me up with fear and worry. Before moving everything was planned and the move happened so smoothly and so effortlessly, it was like I was doing everything in Devine order. Now that I’m in deep, I’m being attacked in all directions. Questioning my next move, haven’t touched a microphone since I got here and on top of that financially stressing, my kids are still adjusting to the schools here, my youngest encountered her first group of bullies and didn’t want to go to school… no family to help me when I fall, just me and mine… its so much. But I’m learning to change my way of thinking… I’ve been through worse and I literally lost everything once and got it back triple.  So yeah it’s scary but I always pull through. My thought process is maturing. It’s a lot I’m dealing with internally, but I refuse to be broken. I prayed to GOD and asked him to guide my steps, no matter where that may lead me I’m trusting him and only him. When you make the choice to walk by faith, and not by sight, you will encounter all kinds of things to throw you off. I am a vessel and I know that GOD won’t put more on me than I can bare. I’m gone keep pushing baby… when I moved it was so many people telling me “oh you’ll be back” and in a sense I felt it was a way to pray on my downfall, but then I learned that people will instill their own fears upon you, because they couldn’t do it, or they no someone who couldn’t do it they don’t believe you can or don’t want you to. I love my new home, I love the people, the southern hospitality, the opportunities and I know this is where I’m suppose to be. This song always brings me to a sane place. “MAKE ME OVER” by @bribabineaux 
I hope it blesses someone this Sunday cause it always makes me feel better. HAPPY SUNDAY MY LOVES AND MAKE TODAY AND EVERYDAY COUNT. God bless 😘
